ining initial-value\nsimulations of fastest-growing eigenmodes, the predictions for mass-ratio\nscaling are tested and verified numerically for a range of collision\nfrequencies. Insights from the small electron-to-ion mass ratio theory may lead\nto a computationally efficient treatment of extended modes.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 5 Aug 2021 19:22:01 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 26 Jan 2022 09:12:04 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-01-27"}
